    <title type="html"><![CDATA[GitHub page]]></title>
    <link href="http://kAworu.github.io/octopress/blog/2013/11/23/github-page/"/>
    <updated>2013-11-23T14:39:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://kAworu.github.io/octopress/blog/2013/11/23/github-page</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img class="no-border pull-right" src="http://kAworu.github.io/octopress/images/GitHub-Mark.png" title="GitHub logo" ></p>

<p>There is <a href="http://kAworu.github.io/octopress/github-page-example">a new &ldquo;GitHub Page&rdquo;</a> kinda like
the GitHub sidebar, but with more extensive informations.</p>

<p>It has been based on <a href="http://carlboettiger.info/software.html">this one</a> but modified in order to ouput bootstrap
classes (and also use the GitHub account information from octopress config). As
such, it can be used with any octopress/boostrap3 theme (and only a very few
modifications are needed to &ldquo;untie&rdquo; it from octopress).</p>

<p>If it suits you, the page&rsquo;s source (as all this blog&rsquo;s code) can be found
<a href="https://github.com/kAworu/octopress/blob/octostrap3-demo/source/github-page-example/index.html">here</a>. In addition to Bootstrap3 &amp; jQuery, you&rsquo;ll need <code>strftime.js</code>.</p>

<p>Kudo to Jean Pierre for the idea :)</p>
]]></content>
